Kongstrup!

01:45:33.527 --> 01:45:35.836
Come out and talk to me!

01:45:38.007 --> 01:45:40.282
I'm here to collect
the money, Kongstrup!

01:45:41.327 --> 01:45:42.362
Kongstrup!

01:46:01.407 --> 01:46:02.760
Look who it is!

01:46:05.127 --> 01:46:06.606
Let me say hello to you.

01:46:09.007 --> 01:46:11.441
Are you too proud to
say hello to me?

01:46:12.687 --> 01:46:14.086
Do you think that you're better?

01:46:15.607 --> 01:46:17.837
Is it because you're leaving
to have your bastard son...

01:46:18.007 --> 01:46:20.840
...on the other side of the sea,
while I had mine in a turnip patch?

01:46:21.007 --> 01:46:23.043
But it was the same
old whoremonger.

01:46:23.247 --> 01:46:25.044
The same whoremonger as ever!

01:46:27.367 --> 01:46:29.437
Signe, Signe.

01:46:29.847 --> 01:46:30.996
Signe.

01:46:31.167 --> 01:46:33.283
Would you tell him that
I need the money?

01:46:33.447 --> 01:46:35.165
Why do you leave evil eye?

01:46:35.327 --> 01:46:37.363
I warned you!

01:46:37.527 --> 01:46:39.518
Let me go! Let me go!

01:46:39.687 --> 01:46:43.316
Kongstrup, come on and help
you're old sweetheart!

01:46:43.807 --> 01:46:44.876
Let me go!

01:46:45.047 --> 01:46:46.002
Let me go!

01:46:46.167 --> 01:46:48.123
Let me go!

01:47:52.647 --> 01:47:54.319
What do you stare?

01:48:09.647 --> 01:48:12.525
If I've to search for you once more...
- Sorry madame.

01:48:29.647 --> 01:48:31.126
It beats me.

01:48:31.767 --> 01:48:35.123
I would have thought that only
dead could end such grief.

01:48:36.047 --> 01:48:38.083
She must have an iron grip on herself

01:49:51.127 --> 01:49:52.845
Wake up! Send the doctor, quick!

01:49:56.487 --> 01:49:57.602
What is it papa?

01:49:58.247 --> 01:50:01.080
Dear Jesus! It must be something bad.

01:50:07.567 --> 01:50:11.082
What is it?
- It's so awful.

01:50:11.247 --> 01:50:12.043
What is it?

01:50:13.367 --> 01:50:15.119
What? What did you say?

01:50:15.287 --> 01:50:17.118
She cut...!
- What is it?

01:50:19.127 --> 01:50:20.082
What happened?
- Kongstrup.

01:50:20.247 --> 01:50:21.805
What?
- He's bleeding.

01:50:21.967 --> 01:50:23.878
We should get some help.
- Really?

01:51:07.407 --> 01:51:08.362
It's fun!

01:51:48.927 --> 01:51:51.521
Mister Freeze, could you
tell us what this means?

01:51:51.687 --> 01:51:55.441
Pelle is the young cuckoo
in missus Olson's nest.

01:51:57.647 --> 01:51:59.638
Ins't she married to a seaman?

01:51:59.807 --> 01:52:01.286
He's captain Olson's bride.

01:52:01.447 --> 01:52:03.517
Your father doesn't care
about that, does he?

01:52:03.767 --> 01:52:05.883
He's captain Olson's bride.

01:52:06.047 --> 01:52:08.686
Your father doesn't care
about that, does he?

01:52:08.847 --> 01:52:10.565
Watch out! Watch out!

01:52:10.727 --> 01:52:13.116
Any girl would like to marry
a man like that.

01:52:13.287 --> 01:52:15.278
What if her husband
comes back, Pelle?

01:52:32.367 --> 01:52:34.119
Guess what Pelle?

01:52:34.287 --> 01:52:35.879
This is for Captain Olson!

01:52:46.767 --> 01:52:49.600
Just you wait Pelle,
we're gonna get you.

01:53:20.727 --> 01:53:21.876
Pelle.

01:53:23.887 --> 01:53:26.321
I've thinking a lot
about the situation.

01:53:29.287 --> 01:53:32.199
You and I would be welcome
at missus Olson's.

01:53:35.767 --> 01:53:37.405
We could move right in.

01:53:44.527 --> 01:53:45.926
I mean...

01:53:46.407 --> 01:53:50.195
It's against the law to
move in with a woman who's married.

01:53:51.327 --> 01:53:53.602
But...

01:53:54.567 --> 01:53:57.764
I want some comfort.

01:54:00.607 --> 01:54:03.485
We could make it look like
the two of us are labourers.

01:54:07.247 --> 01:54:10.045
She could sew you new clothes.

01:54:10.447 --> 01:54:12.278
Wouldn't it be nice to
have new underwear?

01:54:15.127 --> 01:54:16.355
lf...

01:54:16.847 --> 01:54:18.678
...I did move in with missus Olson...

01:54:19.327 --> 01:54:21.318
...you did move in with missus Olson?

01:54:25.087 --> 01:54:27.726
It's a lot easier for you.
Is all ahead of you.

01:54:27.927 --> 01:54:30.122
Your whole future to make
something happen.

01:54:30.367 --> 01:54:32.005
I need someone to take care of me.

01:54:32.927 --> 01:54:35.043
I'll run away if you move in.

01:54:36.567 --> 01:54:39.081
You have to grow
old to say that to me.

01:54:39.287 --> 01:54:40.561
Just look what you're doing?

01:54:40.727 --> 01:54:42.206
Someone else will have
to fill in the holes.

01:54:42.367 --> 01:54:44.881
So the foreman doesn't find you out.

01:54:45.087 --> 01:54:46.679
Stop that right now.

01:54:46.927 --> 01:54:50.044
I don't make acarving of you
and missus Olson in bed.

01:54:50.207 --> 01:54:52.118
You're getting a little so far.
Come back here!

01:54:52.407 --> 01:54:56.366
You'd better watch out I don't
send the foreman on you.

01:55:06.807 --> 01:55:07.717
Pelle!

01:55:09.647 --> 01:55:10.523
Pelle!

01:55:11.927 --> 01:55:12.996
Pelle!

01:55:15.407 --> 01:55:16.760
Could you go by missus Olson's...

01:55:16.927 --> 01:55:18.883
...on your way back from school?

01:55:20.807 --> 01:55:23.116
This is something she's
going to mend for us.

01:55:25.127 --> 01:55:27.800
And be sure to tell her
I'll come by this evening.

01:55:28.287 --> 01:55:30.960
Why don't you marry her, papa?

01:55:31.647 --> 01:55:33.877
Pelle, I will.

01:55:34.767 --> 01:55:37.201
But we've got to deal with
the country's authorities.

01:55:38.647 --> 01:55:41.400
Missus Olson needs a dead
certificate from the government.

01:55:42.727 --> 01:55:45.287
But soon we'll have coffee and bed.

01:56:03.687 --> 01:56:06.918
It's missus Olson's young cuckoo!

01:56:29.567 --> 01:56:31.717
Let's see how tough you are, Pelle.

01:56:33.247 --> 01:56:34.646
To the sea with him!

01:56:35.087 --> 01:56:36.645
Run cuckoo bird!
- Run!

01:56:57.407 --> 01:56:59.363
Come on, let's see you dance!

01:56:59.527 --> 01:57:02.166
Run cuckoo bird!

01:57:08.327 --> 01:57:10.602
Come back to Sweden!

01:57:10.767 --> 01:57:12.166
Go away, cuckoo bird!

01:57:12.327 --> 01:57:14.283
Away, away, away, away!

01:57:15.767 --> 01:57:18.406
Away, away, away!

01:57:19.127 --> 01:57:22.756
Away, away, away. Come on!

01:58:45.047 --> 01:58:46.685
Look! It's Captain Olson!

01:59:15.247 --> 01:59:16.202
You're at home already.

01:59:22.487 --> 01:59:24.876
Missus's Olson husband
has come home.

02:00:37.567 --> 02:00:41.003
I will stay here forever...

02:00:41.527 --> 02:00:43.438
...standing here like...

02:00:44.167 --> 02:00:46.203
...a block of hay in the shed.

02:00:47.287 --> 02:00:49.198
I was only looking for a home...

02:00:49.967 --> 02:00:51.923
...to spend my old age.

02:00:52.927 --> 02:00:56.203
I've found someone and I felt free.

02:00:57.967 --> 02:00:59.286
Jesus!

02:01:01.207 --> 02:01:02.845
Jesus, help!

02:02:18.847 --> 02:02:21.236
What the hell is the point of crying?

02:02:23.567 --> 02:02:25.683
I want you to meet my new sweetheart.

02:02:28.047 --> 02:02:29.765
Here, Pelle.

02:02:36.287 --> 02:02:37.766
I forgot...

02:02:39.007 --> 02:02:41.726
...that you didn't this thing.
You're too fine.

02:02:42.687 --> 02:02:44.803
It doesn't help going around...

02:02:44.967 --> 02:02:46.798
...whimpering.

02:02:52.807 --> 02:02:53.796
Papa!

02:02:56.767 --> 02:02:58.678
It's sleepery.

02:03:02.927 --> 02:03:04.997
This is a little devil.

02:03:11.047 --> 02:03:12.480
You're crying?

02:03:15.327 --> 02:03:17.238
If some do something to you...

02:03:18.207 --> 02:03:22.200
...tell them that your father is
Lasse, from Tommelilla.

02:03:22.527 --> 02:03:25.360
It's alright, your father is here.

02:03:25.767 --> 02:03:29.123
And your father can stand
on his own two feet.

02:03:33.607 --> 02:03:35.996
I'm going out to the big house.

02:03:37.687 --> 02:03:39.518
Now the bastard is gonna...

02:03:39.687 --> 02:03:41.678
...have to answer for all these years

02:03:42.407 --> 02:03:44.716
We are going to have a
little talk with the missus.

02:03:44.927 --> 02:03:46.485
I won't let you go out there!

02:04:27.927 --> 02:04:29.076
Erik.

02:04:30.927 --> 02:04:31.803
Erik.

02:04:34.367 --> 02:04:35.243
Erik.

02:04:37.607 --> 02:04:39.802
Spring is coming, that's
what papa says.

02:04:41.607 --> 02:04:43.279
In the spring you'll be...

02:04:44.327 --> 02:04:45.282
...a free man.

02:04:47.247 --> 02:04:48.202
Think of it.

02:04:50.487 --> 02:04:52.523
Then, we can leave this awful place.

02:04:54.727 --> 02:04:56.524
And go out and conquer the world.

02:05:20.527 --> 02:05:21.880
Pelle.

02:05:23.967 --> 02:05:25.639
What is it they all talk about?

02:05:26.247 --> 02:05:27.726
I wouldn't know.

02:05:28.767 --> 02:05:30.359
You haven't heard anything?

02:05:31.287 --> 02:05:34.757
Do you think I wanna go to class
so they can laugh at me some more?

02:05:50.807 --> 02:05:53.526
I know I drink too much.

02:05:54.847 --> 02:05:58.203
But it's difficult not to, when
you're heart is broken.

02:06:03.767 --> 02:06:04.643
Pelle...

02:06:06.087 --> 02:06:09.921
...if I promise you'll never again se
me the way I was yesterday...

02:06:10.647 --> 02:06:12.558
...would you agree to go to school?

02:06:12.727 --> 02:06:13.921
Tomorrow, Pelle?

02:06:14.847 --> 02:06:16.121
Because if you don't...

02:06:18.247 --> 02:06:19.475
...then they will force you.

02:06:19.807 --> 02:06:22.196
There'll be a lot of trouble
with the authority.

02:06:25.607 --> 02:06:27.677
Alright? Say yes.

02:06:30.447 --> 02:06:33.086
10 times 10 is a hundred

02:06:33.487 --> 02:06:36.877
100 times 10 is a thousand.

02:06:37.047 --> 02:06:39.925
100 divided by 10 is 10.

02:06:40.087 --> 02:06:42.920
1000 divided by 10 is 100.

02:06:51.887 --> 02:06:53.081
Mister Freeze?

02:06:53.367 --> 02:06:54.516
Mister Freeze.

02:06:55.407 --> 02:06:56.522
He's asleep.

02:06:56.807 --> 02:06:58.525
Mister Freeze, it's time.

02:07:08.127 --> 02:07:09.082
Sir.

02:07:10.047 --> 02:07:11.924
It's time to go home.

02:08:15.287 --> 02:08:17.084
Pelle, where's your father?

02:08:20.567 --> 02:08:21.761
Fooling around?

02:08:24.487 --> 02:08:26.205
My father would be happy...

02:08:26.367 --> 02:08:29.040
...to marry your father to captain
Olson's second wife.

02:08:36.447 --> 02:08:38.358
Help papa! Help!

02:08:42.527 --> 02:08:45.724
You scoundrel!
How dare you hit my son!

02:08:46.687 --> 02:08:49.247
You're going to hear from
the authorities about this!

02:08:55.287 --> 02:08:56.436
Pelle, Pelle, Pelle...

02:08:56.607 --> 02:08:59.724
That was about the worst you
could do, hit the minister's son.

02:09:00.607 --> 02:09:02.643
The town's minister.

02:09:02.967 --> 02:09:05.117
He deserved it, I'm sure.

02:09:05.287 --> 02:09:07.960
But still you shouldn't have done it.
What else did he do to you?

02:09:08.447 --> 02:09:11.678
He said he could get you married
at boatsman Olson's second wife.

02:09:12.967 --> 02:09:14.082
He did?

02:09:15.847 --> 02:09:16.962
He did?

02:09:18.087 --> 02:09:22.046
If I had him here,
I'd rip his innards out.

02:09:22.447 --> 02:09:23.482
Do you feel revenged?

02:09:23.687 --> 02:09:24.722
No, not really.

02:09:25.447 --> 02:09:28.803
His father came and gave
what he deserved.

02:09:28.967 --> 02:09:30.036
Revenge.

02:09:31.487 --> 02:09:33.876
It's a bad situation.

02:09:35.927 --> 02:09:38.077
And you don't intend to apologize?

02:09:39.167 --> 02:09:40.885
No, no, you shouldn't.

02:09:44.247 --> 02:09:47.364
Although maybe you should...
No, no.

02:09:48.127 --> 02:09:49.606
You have to twist and turn...

02:09:50.447 --> 02:09:52.085
...as the eel said in the frying pan.

02:09:56.927 --> 02:09:59.282
We are very sorry to bother you...

02:09:59.447 --> 02:10:02.007
We have no choice, but...

02:10:02.407 --> 02:10:03.999
...to ask for your help.

02:10:05.047 --> 02:10:06.844
Did you blow your nose properly?

02:10:08.687 --> 02:10:10.803
We are very sorry to bother you, Sir.

02:10:11.327 --> 02:10:12.521
I'm very sorry.

02:10:19.567 --> 02:10:21.558
There's probably no one home.
- Let's go in.

02:10:21.887 --> 02:10:23.525
We can't stand here all day.

02:10:23.687 --> 02:10:26.679
Go first, if you think you
can handle this better.

02:10:28.167 --> 02:10:29.395
Come in.

02:10:31.127 --> 02:10:32.560
Good day.

02:10:32.967 --> 02:10:34.366
Good day.

02:10:36.487 --> 02:10:38.318
It's like this...

02:10:40.447 --> 02:10:43.678
I hope the proprietor
be angry with us.

02:10:45.647 --> 02:10:47.160
He won't be angry.

02:10:52.047 --> 02:10:53.924
You must forgive us for coming here...

02:10:54.087 --> 02:10:56.476
...to talk about something which
has nothing to do with the farm.

02:10:57.207 --> 02:10:58.435
But...

02:11:00.727 --> 02:11:02.683
...when the father's sins...

02:11:03.367 --> 02:11:05.198
...are visited upon his son.

02:11:06.247 --> 02:11:07.566
Then...

02:11:07.727 --> 02:11:09.558
Then...
- Why are you standing?

02:11:10.487 --> 02:11:11.556
Sit down, please.

02:11:11.727 --> 02:11:13.479
Thank you.
- Why you haven't...

02:11:13.647 --> 02:11:14.841
...offered them a sit, dear?

02:11:23.487 --> 02:11:25.398
Thank you.
- What is it?

02:11:26.407 --> 02:11:27.396
You need money?

02:11:27.927 --> 02:11:29.724
No, it's...

02:11:30.247 --> 02:11:31.680
Is just like a...

02:11:32.327 --> 02:11:34.045
It's just that...

02:11:37.727 --> 02:11:39.877
I hope that you won't be angry but...

02:11:41.447 --> 02:11:42.846
...it's...

02:11:43.727 --> 02:11:45.001
It's the boy.

02:11:45.887 --> 02:11:47.605
They're going to send him away.

02:11:48.247 --> 02:11:49.521
Send him away?
- Yes.

02:11:49.727 --> 02:11:50.876
¿ What have you done?

02:11:57.567 --> 02:11:59.364
I beat up the minister's son.

02:12:00.687 --> 02:12:01.881
And why you did you do that?

02:12:06.007 --> 02:12:08.237
Because he said evil
things about Lasse.

02:12:09.767 --> 02:12:10.836
What did he say?

02:12:12.167 --> 02:12:15.125
He called me...

02:12:16.967 --> 02:12:19.720
He called me Mrs. Olson's plaything.

02:12:20.327 --> 02:12:22.636
You know, the kids...

02:12:28.327 --> 02:12:29.521
I was...

02:12:30.607 --> 02:12:32.279
...Mrs. Olson's sweetheart.

02:12:32.447 --> 02:12:34.642
Because everyone thought
she was a widow.

02:12:37.167 --> 02:12:40.284
And other day her husband
came home from the sea.

02:12:43.447 --> 02:12:44.562
Here.

02:12:46.967 --> 02:12:50.198
And the boy made Pelle furious.
- Yes, unfortunately.

02:12:51.127 --> 02:12:52.276
That's how it is.

02:12:52.447 --> 02:12:53.277
With poor wretches...

02:12:53.447 --> 02:12:55.517
...they're only there to be pecked at

02:12:55.687 --> 02:12:58.247
Well, I prefer the bird that pecks
back and defends his nest...

02:12:58.447 --> 02:13:00.244
...regardless of the poor it is.

02:13:01.887 --> 02:13:05.516
I'll do what I can.
Don't worry about it anymore.

02:13:05.767 --> 02:13:06.722
Thank you.

02:13:08.927 --> 02:13:09.916
By the way.

02:13:10.647 --> 02:13:12.842
My husband and I decided...

02:13:13.087 --> 02:13:17.080
...the young assistant to
our foreman will be leaving.

02:13:17.647 --> 02:13:21.401
Maybe Pelle would like to
become his replacement.

02:13:26.047 --> 02:13:27.446
Thank you.

02:13:27.727 --> 02:13:29.445
Say thank you.

02:13:43.087 --> 02:13:46.557
Almost as if she thought
it was her own idea?

02:13:46.847 --> 02:13:48.644
She thought, she thought it herself.

02:13:50.767 --> 02:13:51.995
Your recognized this?

02:13:52.647 --> 02:13:54.877
They're a bit big, but
we'll stuff them with papers.

02:13:55.047 --> 02:13:56.400
Try them on.

02:14:01.767 --> 02:14:04.122
I'll get some boot wax,
and they'll be like new.

02:14:05.287 --> 02:14:06.959
Now let's have a look.

02:14:11.727 --> 02:14:15.276
Stand up straight. I want
you stand very straight.

02:14:15.487 --> 02:14:18.240
Shoulders back and
chin a little forward.

02:14:18.407 --> 02:14:20.557
Not like that. Lift you chin a little

02:14:20.727 --> 02:14:23.082
Now a sharp look in the eye.

02:14:23.727 --> 02:14:25.797
You must command respect for yourself

02:14:27.007 --> 02:14:29.475
The way you stand and the look
in your eye. That's what does it.

02:14:33.127 --> 02:14:36.039
Let the others labour.
You give the orders.

02:14:37.047 --> 02:14:38.400
You can't take tonight off!

02:14:38.567 --> 02:14:40.080
Clean now the cow down!

02:14:42.047 --> 02:14:43.082
And Pelle...

02:14:44.247 --> 02:14:46.158
Maybe you'll get to eat
sunday dinner with the proprietor.

02:14:46.327 --> 02:14:49.558
And have a napkin-ring
with your name on it.

02:14:50.047 --> 02:14:51.366
Pelle Karlsson.

02:15:03.527 --> 02:15:07.122
And who knows, Pelle. Maybe
one day you'll be the foreman.

02:15:07.487 --> 02:15:11.275
I could tell you the way she
was thinking it was perfect.

02:15:37.567 --> 02:15:38.841
Erik!

02:15:43.247 --> 02:15:44.521
Erik!

02:15:47.807 --> 02:15:49.320
Erik!

02:15:50.127 --> 02:15:51.526
Wait for me!

02:15:54.367 --> 02:15:55.686
Erik!

02:16:20.487 --> 02:16:21.886
I don't want it.

02:16:26.567 --> 02:16:28.285
We must leave here, papa.

02:16:28.807 --> 02:16:30.286
Now.

02:17:00.527 --> 02:17:01.562
It's Karna.

02:17:01.727 --> 02:17:03.046
I get here in time.

02:17:03.727 --> 02:17:05.843
I was afraid the foreman
and the missus would see me.

02:17:07.127 --> 02:17:08.639
A gift for you.

02:17:09.246 --> 02:17:10.726
It's a down quilt.

02:17:10.967 --> 02:17:14.198
It'll keep you warm. No matter
where you end up in the world.

02:17:15.447 --> 02:17:16.674
Bye, Gabriela.

02:17:20.647 --> 02:17:21.841
Bye, Blanca.

02:17:22.367 --> 02:17:23.846
You'll be a good girl.

02:17:33.486 --> 02:17:34.966
Well, Aspasia.

02:17:35.566 --> 02:17:37.364
Time to say goodbye to Pelle.

02:17:37.927 --> 02:17:39.996
He is going up to see the world.

02:17:47.927 --> 02:17:49.155
Papa.

02:17:55.447 --> 02:17:56.721
What is it?

02:18:04.566 --> 02:18:06.000
Can't we stay?

02:18:33.486 --> 02:18:35.205
You'll have to go
without me, Pelle.

02:18:36.727 --> 02:18:38.683
I don't have the strength anymore.

02:18:38.967 --> 02:18:40.958
I'm too old. It's the reason.

02:18:42.527 --> 02:18:43.925
Too old.

02:18:46.166 --> 02:18:47.805
There's no future for an old man.

02:18:51.527 --> 02:18:52.754
Do you understand that?

02:19:12.047 --> 02:19:13.958
I'll make a bundle for you.

02:19:14.607 --> 02:19:17.599
You can have 2 of
my shirts then you have 4.

02:19:18.767 --> 02:19:20.644
Then one you're wearing is clean.

02:19:21.447 --> 02:19:24.007
And remember: never wear
it more than two weeks...

02:19:24.166 --> 02:19:26.522
...at a time, otherwise you
get bad name in town.

02:19:26.807 --> 02:19:29.321
And change your socks
before they wear out.

02:19:29.486 --> 02:19:31.442
Keep your clothes clean.
Keep your good name.

02:19:31.647 --> 02:19:34.366
You save half the work and all shames

02:19:39.246 --> 02:19:41.282
You can have my boots too.

02:19:43.807 --> 02:19:45.798
They are a bit worn.

02:19:49.527 --> 02:19:51.119
And here's the Bible.

02:19:55.367 --> 02:19:57.403
Your mohter said
I was to give it to you...

02:19:57.807 --> 02:20:00.002
...on the day she went
out to the world.

02:20:29.527 --> 02:20:33.122
Next time we'll meet maybe
there'll be a proper home for you.

02:20:38.087 --> 02:20:39.805
Say Karna goodbye.

02:20:49.127 --> 02:20:50.526
Goodbye, papa.

02:20:52.767 --> 02:20:53.643
Thank you.

